            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="indent(8)">
                <placeName>Montreal</placeName>
                <date>6 Jany 53</date>
            </p>
            <p>Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Your favor of the <date>11th dec</date> came in due<lb/> course with
                    <date>Dec</date> Occidents its too early to look for<lb/> the <date>Jany</date>
                No's I enclose herein the Amount<lb/> of <persName>Mr. G. Benjamin's</persName> dues
                which I have, at length<lb/> succeeded in obtainingâ€”as yet all I have been<lb/> able
                to collect. You do not seem to be aware<lb/> that <persName>Mr Desola</persName> is
                republishing his Prayer books in<lb/>
                <placeName>London</placeName>. At least the volume is printed. I have not<lb/> heard
                the price. But as nearly all the members of<lb/> this congregation visit
                    <placeName>England</placeName> very frequently<lb/> they will be apt to provide
                themselves with setts<lb/> there. Which they are enabled to bring out without<lb/>
                any expense. I also notice some cheap editions<lb/> of the Bible advertised in the
                Chronicle.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Your a/ct was sent to <persName>Mr Levy</persName> who informs<lb/>
                me that he paid for the Books_but that he would<lb/> transmit the Bill to
                    <persName>Mr Lyons</persName>â€”you must hear in<lb/> mind that having admitted
                that you had claimed<lb/> from <persName>Mr Lyons</persName> entirely relieves
                    <persName>Mr Levy</persName> from any<lb/> objection to pay again for the Books.
                He leaves<lb/> tomorrow for <placeName>Europe</placeName>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Dr. David</persName> held in intercourse with the
                Editor<lb/> of the Asmoneon. His work was sent, I believe,<lb/> after the lapse of
                some time to numerous Editors</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p>in the <placeName>United States</placeName> and heard it preached<lb/> that of two
                Jewish publications-notice was taken<lb/> of it in one only. As you profess to
                record events<lb/> connected with our people it was thought singular<lb/> that the
                only work published in <placeName>Canada</placeName> of the<lb/> kind would have
                been considered beneath<lb/> your notice.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Winter has but just commenced &amp; the <placeName>St
                    Lawrence</placeName><lb/> was yesterday frozen over. Within a week we have<lb/>
                had enough snow for a season. You would be<lb/> better off here than at
                    <placeName>St. Louis</placeName> (as we have only<lb/> to cross the River to
                reach Railroads to all<lb/> parts of the <placeName>United States</placeName>. You
                did not<lb/> state the cost of some books you forwarded for the<lb/> Sunday School
                please let me know that I may send<lb/> you the Amount.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I enclose thirty Dollars say pee<add>?</add> of Order for
                    <date>1851</date> &amp; <date>1852</date>. 1.10.0<lb/>
                <persName>G Benjamin</persName>
                <date>1846</date>.<date>1847</date>.<date>1848</date>.<date>1849</date>.<date>1850</date>.<date>1851</date>
                &amp; <date>1852</date> = 7 years</p>
            <p><add>?</add>: c15/ &amp; publications 18/9Â Â Â Â Â 5.18.9</p>
            <p><persName>Kahen</persName>/<placeName>Toronto</placeName> paid in full for 6 mo's
                having left the<lb/> province 5 <add>?</add> subscriber since
                <date>Oct</date>Â Â Â Â Â 0.7.6</p>
            <p>or $31.75 leaving $1/4 to be accounted forÂ Â Â Â Â 7.16.3</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Please acknowledge rect of subscriptions from <persName>Goodman<lb/>
                    Benjamin's</persName>
                <add>?</add> in our next Occident<lb/>
                <persName>Mr <add>?</add></persName><lb/> &amp;Remain yr Srvt</p>
